<Base title="Privacy Policy | CoverToday Insurance" description="CoverToday Insurance Agency privacy policy: what we collect, how we use it, SMS consent and data sharing, your privacy choices, and how to contact us.">
  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="sub">How CoverToday Insurance Agency collects, uses, and protects your information.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section><div class="wrap" style="max-width:820px">
    <p style="color:var(--muted)">Effective date: January 9, 2025 · Last updated: July 2, 2026</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Privacy statement</h2>
    <p>At CoverToday Insurance Agency ("we," "us," or "our"), your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share your information through our website (www.covertoday.com), telephone communications ((310) 299-5555), text messaging, online advertisements, and other online and offline interactions. It applies solely to our systems and does not extend to third-party sites.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Information we collect</h2>
    <p><strong>Information you provide directly:</strong> name, address, email, phone number, date of birth, driver’s license, marital status and household information; insurance details such as previous policies, coverages, claims history; and billing information needed to place coverage.</p>
    <p><strong>Information collected automatically:</strong> device details (IP address, browser type, operating system), usage data (pages viewed, search queries), and cookies or similar technologies used to improve your experience and analyze usage.</p>
    <p><strong>Information from third parties:</strong> consumer reporting agencies (credit history, driving records, claims data) and insurance-support organizations that assist with policy underwriting and claims.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">How we use your information</h2>
    <p>We use your information to provide insurance quotes, process applications, and manage policies; communicate with you about your account and policy updates; analyze and improve our services; ensure the security of our systems and comply with legal requirements; and prevent fraud and unauthorized access.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">How we share your information</h2>
    <p>We may share information with service providers that assist in policy processing, claims management, and customer communications; with insurance carriers to quote and place your coverage; for legal or safety reasons, to comply with legal obligations or respond to regulatory inquiries; and with your consent for additional uses that require explicit approval.</p>
    <p><strong>We never sell your personal information.</strong></p>

    <h2 class="sec">SMS / text messaging &amp; mobile information</h2>
    <p>If you opt in to receive text messages from CoverToday Insurance Agency (a DBA of Univision Insurance Services LLC), we may send messages related to quotes, policy service, appointment reminders, and — if you separately consent — promotional offers.</p>
    <p><strong>No mobile information will be shared with third parties or affiliates for marketing or promotional purposes.</strong> Text messaging originator opt-in data and consent will not be shared with any third parties, except as necessary to deliver the messages (e.g., our SMS service provider).</p>
    <p>You may opt out at any time by replying <strong>STOP</strong> to any message, or reply <strong>HELP</strong> for assistance. Message and data rates may apply; message frequency may vary. See our <a href="/sms-terms">SMS Terms &amp; Conditions</a> for full details.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Your privacy choices</h2>
    <p>You may unsubscribe from marketing emails by following the instructions in our emails or contacting us at (310) 299-5555. To opt out of text messages, reply STOP to any message. You can adjust your browser settings to limit the use of cookies; note that disabling cookies may affect website functionality.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Security of your information</h2>
    <p>We use industry-standard measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or storage is completely secure. Please contact us immediately if you believe your information has been compromised.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Children’s privacy</h2>
    <p>Our services are not intended for children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child, we will delete it promptly.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">State-specific rights</h2>
    <p><strong>California residents:</strong> under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), you have the right to request information about how your data is used, request deletion of your personal data (subject to exceptions), and opt out of the sale of your personal information (we do not sell personal information). Residents of other states with specific privacy laws may have additional rights — contact us to learn more.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Updates to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The date of the most recent update is listed at the top of this page.</p>

    <h2 class="sec">Contact us</h2>
    <p>CoverToday Insurance Agency, 272 S Rampart Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90057 · (310) 299-5555 · <a href="mailto:info@covertoday.com">info@covertoday.com</a> · CA DOI License #0K77310.</p>
  </div></section>
</Base>
